<br>
Obviously the PoJ flag has to be 6 people... so that can be done at anytime with the correct people.  When I did the trial we had the following group: Wizard, Enchanter, Cleric, Shaman, Warrior and myself (Monk)  All were 65 except the wizard who was 62.<br>
<br>
The strategy was for the enchanter to AE Stun, while the Wizard AE nuked, the Shaman AE slowed.  The main tank would pick a target, I would assist main tank, cleric would cover any heals necessary, and I believe also the shaman assisted and high-slowed the main target.<br>
<br>
Rinse, Repeat and hope mana holds out until the final encounter...<br>
<br>
I've done the Behemoth 4 times, with 2 successes and 2 failures.  Let me stress right off the bat, that this encounter is EXTREMELY hard.  We would need atleast 4 high level enchanters and 4 high level druids to even attempt this encounter.  The situation with the Behemoth is that if any of the rats/spiders come into the room while you're fighting the Behemoth, its a 3k damage AE plus other crud. (Depending on the AE he uses)  So obviously, you all die quickly if they get in.  So you need to position the enchanter/druid suicide squads at each corner of the room to root/mezz/charm/snare whatever all rats/spiders so nothing gets into the room.<br>
<br>
I can tell you that even with 35 people, level 64 average we still failed.. so we would need an almost flawless turnout of everyone we've got to be able to do that.  But if you win, you get access to the Plane of Tactics which is an awesome zone.<br>
<br>
